{meta: title You are my flower}
{meta: artist Earl Scruggs and Lester Flatt}
{meta: composer A. P. Carter}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]When summertime is gone
[D7]And snow begins to fall
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
You can sing this song
[G]And say to one and all
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
You are my flower
[D7]That's blooming in the mountain so high
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
You are my flower
[G]That's blooming there for me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
So wear a happy smile
[D7]And life will be worthwhile
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Forget the tears
[G]But don't forget to smile
{end_of_verse}
